The paper discusses a machine learning approach to reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on designing an activation function that produces sparse representations, which is a common topic in machine learning and neural networks (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks in both discrete-action control environments and continuous-action environments, which are common topics in robotics and control (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper includes experiments with image-based environments, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper uses neural networks with sparse representations to improve learning, which is a common topic in neural engineering (cs.NE).
